-- DriverWorkitems / TernaryBuildZ3 isolation — the ternary null-operand
-- regression (sample-ternary-crash-diagnosis.md).
--
-- The C2Ite build step calls TernaryBuildZ3 with the top three handle-
-- stack entries. When a branch sub-expression never pushed a Z3 AST its
-- handle is 0; the OLD code passed 0 straight to Z3_mk_ite, which derefs
-- null and SIGSEGVs (exit 139). The guard must instead halt NAMEABLY:
-- a 0 operand ⇒ Exit(7). This test feeds a null `then_h` and asserts the
-- kernel exits 7 cleanly — if the guard regressed, the kernel would pass
-- 0 to Z3_mk_ite and crash (a non-7 / signal exit), failing the test.
--
-- entry: main
-- expect: exit = 7
import "stdlib/kernel.ev"
import "compiler2/translate2_bool.ev"

claim main
    e_ite ∈ Effect
    TernaryBuildZ3(ctx_h ↦ 1, cond_h ↦ 99, then_h ↦ 0, else_h ↦ 42, eff ↦ e_ite)
    effects ∈ Seq(Effect) = ⟨e_ite⟩
